casebody.data:
[Hillsborougli,

June, 1884.] Preston, Adm'r, v. Cutter, Ex'r, Ap't. Preston, Adm'r, v. Monroe & a., Ap'ts. Gr. B. French and Jeremiah Smith, for the plaintiff. F. S. & H. C. Cutter, for the defendants. *617Smith, J.

We decline to express any opinion on the case as now presented. The facts agreed are so meagre and indefinite that it is apparent a subsequent trial of substantially the whole case must be had. The facts will be found at the trial term.

All concurred.
